templateVersions.content:
Summarize ONLY information that is genuinely relevant from a commercial perspective.
Focus exclusively on findings that fit one of these categories: 1. Relocations, openings, closures, reorganizations, executive appointments, changes in ownership / shareholders / governance. 2. Acquisitions, mergers, fundraising rounds, financial results, strategic announcements. 3. Incidents or weak signals: cyberattacks, outages, litigation, strikes, communication crises, negative publicity. 4. Projects or announcements about IT, cloud, telecommunications, networking, cybersecurity, digital initiatives, business transformation. 5. Any development that could create a sales opportunity, represent a risk, or be a meaningful topic for customer engagement.
Rules: - Discard rumours, marketing fluff, and routine product launches that do not affecft buying behaviour. -I want you to put make a long review of the news that explain very precisely the news and the potential impact of the news. I want this to be around 20 lines - Group findings under bold category headings; omit any category with no signal. - Cite the source URL inline next to every claim. - You must put the Date of the news at the beginning - Put only fresh news. - If absolutely nothing relevant is found, return the single sentence: &quot;No commercially relevant news identified this period.&quot; - Put an accent of strong and weak signals. (if any) - if you have more than 2 news just put the 2 biggest news. - the output must be under 40 lines - you don't find news just put "No news" as output. News: {!$SalesforceDataAction:webSearchStream.webSearchSummary}

